SampleComment: GPS: 52.74981, -110.58772. Wind: 9 km/h NW. Waves: 0.02 m. Calm day. Some comp sites were difficult to locate due to not having bath map. Check for the actual bath map when back in office. Very shallow lake in places and need to find comp sites just off of drops. Microcystin ID: M210084. Probe: 62981. Net: Tow

GPS: 52.74981, -110.58772. Wind: 18 km/h S. Waves:0.05 m. Relatively calm day. Wind pushed us multiple times during the profile reading. So had to back up the boat. Water is quite clear, no cyano observed. Microcystin ID: M210142. Probe: 62981. Net: Tow

GPS: 52.74981, -110.58772. Wind: 15 km/h NW. Waves: 0.1 m. Rick wants 2 copies of Arm Lake in colour. Beautiful morning. Very little activity on the lake. No cyanobacteria noted on the water surface, a few particles in samples. Microcystin ID: M210119. Probe: 62981. Net: Tow

GPS: 52.74981, -110.58772. Wind: 21 km/h SW. Waves: 0.1 m. Slightly gusty day on the lake. Wind blew us away from the profile location mulitple times. We backed up to the location and kept going with profile readings. Minimal cyanobacteria particles noted in the water. Microcystin ID: M210149. Probe: 62981. Net: Tow

GPS: 52.97718, -114.20948. Wind: 3 km/h. Waves: 0 m. Very hot and calm. Lots of particles in the water (phytoplankton) but water was still quite clear (see secchi depth). Sampled with Neil C. Apparantly speed restricted on the lake to protect loons. Microcystin ID: M210085. Probe: 62981. Net: Tow

GPS: 52.97718, -114.20948. Wind: 9 km/h. Waves: 0.02 m. Filament like cyanobacteria noted throughtout the water surface and column. Became more abundant in the North Arm of the lake. Lake was very calm, one other boat on the water. Sediment sample taken at the profile. Microcystin ID: M210097. Probe: 62981. Net: Tow
GPS: 52.97718, -114.20948. Wind: 14 km/h W-SW. Waves: 0.1 m. Aphanizomenon plentiful throughout water column. Water was relatively clear otherwise. Microcystin ID: M210117. Probe: 62981. Net: Tow

GPS: 52.97718, -114.20948. Wind: 7 km/h S-SW. Waves: 0.08 m. Cyanobacteria (Aphanizomenon) particles plentiful throughout water. Streaks on surface and particles. Some accumulation occuring near boat launch and on water surface. Globbules forming in the middle of the lake. Very calm morning. South of boat launch in the middle of the lake big globs of cyanobacteria on surface are senescing. By the end of the day, cyanobacteria is likely to be on shore at boat launch and senescing. Microcystin ID: M210150. Probe: 62981. Net: Tow

GPS: 51.99013, -114.87702. Wind: 2 km/h W-NW. Waves: 0.05 m. Sunny, calm day on the lake. Harold (volunteer) moted that turbidity was sightly higher this June than last. Went too far and hit bottom at 17.6 m before recording 17.5 values (no redox becasue hit bottom). Microcystin ID: M210086. Probe: 62981. Net: Tow

GPS: 51.99013, -114.87702. Wind: 4km/h E. Waves: 0.05 m. Very calm day. Completely overcast with smoke, some mist (has been smoky for last few days). Water is very clear, secchi depth is very deep. Only brought 10 m tubing, so went down as deep as I could to 10.5 m. No algae or cyanobacteria noted through water column. Sediment sample taken at the profile. Microcystin ID: M210098. Probe: 62981. Net: Tow

GPS: 51.99013, -114.87702. Wind: 8 km/h N-NE. Waves: 0.1 m. Can only sample to 10.5 due to tubing. Calm day on the lake. Water is still very clear. Minimal particles in water. Took a sample of milfoil off of volunteer's dock. Microcystin ID: M210100. Probe: 62981. Net: Tow

GPS: 51.99013, -114.87702. Wind: 4 km/h W. Waves: 0.05 m. Beautiful fall morning. Calm and mostly sunny. Minimal particles noted in lake, very clear. Only sampled to 10.5 m due to tubing.  Microcystin ID: M210099. Probe: 62981. Net: Tow
ORP not recorded

GPS: 55.22447, -113.28207. Wind: 2 km/hr N. Waves: 0.1m. Calm morning with very little wind. Sampling with Annette and Angie. Over the past couple weeks the lake had been very windy. Lots of big floating debris in the water such as plants and dead trees. Microcystin ID: M210040. Probe: 49593. Net: Tow

GPS: 55.22447, -113.28207. Wind: 3 km/h E. Waves: 0.2m. Sampling took place in the evening due to forecast the following morning looking windy. Sky was smoky with consistent brightness throughout the day. Some areas of the lake had a greater presense of cyanobacteria (south beach). AIS mussel hauls taken at the profile location, west end and near the PP boat launch. Sampling with Trish Bone and Doug Bone. Sediment haul taken at the profile. Microcystin ID: M210041. Probe: 49593. Net: Tow

GPS: 55.22447, -113.28207. Wind: 16 km/h E. Waves: 0.5 m. 3rd sampling trip on Calling Lake with Bert and Owen. Aphanizomenon all around the lake with the thickest presence on the North-West end. Triplicate G2 taken. AIS hauls taken at the boat launch, west end, and near the PP boat launch. Microcystin ID: M210042. Probe: 49593. Net: Tow

GPS: 55.22447, -113.28207. Wind: 3 km/h NW. Waves: 0.3 m. 4th sampling trip with Micheal and Marie. Lake was very green with cyanobacteria (mostly aphanizomenon) all over. More concentrated in the Southwest side. Very calm morning with lots of pelicans and gulls. Well mixed throughout. Microcystin ID: M210043. Probe: 49593. Net: Tow

GPS: 52.45876, -115.04315. Wind: 6 km/h E-NE. Waves: 0.02 m. Profile location has silt on the bottom approximately 6 meters- may alter depth. No zooplankton in haul, will be interesting to see any further in summer. Profile site need to more further NE to find the deepest spot (52.45889, -115.04170). Microcystin ID: M210110. Probe: 62981. Net: Tow

GPS: 52.45889, -115.04170. Wind: 12 km/h S-SE. Waves 0.05 m. Wind gusts are high (up to 20 km/h) did not impact probe in water, stayed vertical in profile. Very minimal zooplankton in sample (Ron Z. grabbed). Water has low colour. Preformed vertical AIS haul at profile site, and two horizontal hauls at other veliger sites due to shallow depths (1.5 m). Sediment sample taken at the profile. Microcystin ID: M210087. Probe: 62981. Net: Tow

GPS: 52.45889, -115.04170. Wind: 5 km/h S-SE. Waves: 0.01 m. Beautiful, calm day on the lake. Water is much cooler (sampling event followed very rainy and cool day, night time temps are cool). Sampled with Ron Z. using AEP boat. Start hitting silty bottom at 8.4 m hard bottom using tape and weight = 9 m. Water seems around a foot lower than July sampling. Minimal particles observed in the water. Microcystin ID: M210118. Probe: 62981. Net: Tow

GPS: 52.45889, -115.04170. Wind: 7 km/h S-SW. Waves: 0.1 m. Beautiful fall day. Relitively calm, but gusts are quite strong (likely 12 km/h gusts). Lake is wind mixed, very windy month of September. Water is turbid (from wind). Ron Z. assisted in final sampling event. Water appears to have gone down at boat launch ~1 ft. Minimal particles observed in water. Sampled to 1.3 m at most comp sites. Likely sediment in the 8 m. Microcystin ID: M210128. Probe: 62981. Net: Tow

GPS: 56.45564, -111.15713. Wind: 11 km/hr N. Waves: 0.5 m. 1st sampling trip with Ron. Calm on the water. Amorphous colonies in the water but dispersed. Moved 2 of the comp sites, one closer to the input and another in the North side of the lake. Microcystin ID:  M210053. Probe: 49593. Net: Tow

GPS: 56.455656, -111.156995. Wind: 5 km/h NW. Waves: 0.20 m. Hot and smoky day sampling with Brad Bingham. AIS mussel hauls were done at the profile, east basin and the PP boat launch. Sediment haul taken at the profile. Microcystin ID: M210054. Probe: 49593. Net: Tow

GPS: 56.45564, -111.15713. Wind: 22 km/h N. Waves: 0.6 m. 3rd sampling event on Gregoire Lake with Brad Bingham and Tyson Shank. Weather started off nice but wind picked up after the profile. AIS hauls taken at the profile, in the East basin, and at the PP boat launch. G2 QC samples taken in triplicate.  Microcystin ID: M210055. Probe: 49593. Net: Tow

GPS: 54.455656, -111.156995. Wind: 8 km/h SE. Waves: 0.5 m. 4th sampling trip on Gregoire with Brad Bingham and his wife. Water had no large cyanobacteria colonies but the water green hue. Trip started out nice but got rouygh near the end. Drifted from the profile location. Microcystin ID: M210052. Probe: 49593. Net: Tow
ORP not recorded
GPS: 52.54239, -113.99835. Wind: 14 km/h S-SE. Waves: 0.1 m. Beautiful calm morning. 30+ weather in the last 4 days, will be +30 today. Microcystin ID: M210088. Probe: 62981. Net: Tow

GPS: 52.54239, -113.99835. Wind: 12 km/h NW. Waves: 0.01 m. Smoky and overcast day. Smoke has been very thick for the last few days. Lots of spots on the lake with foam bubbles on the surface. Slight fishy smell in some locations on the lake. Very low secchi depth. Sampling event followed a strong storm last night with 50 km/h winds and hail that may have turned up the lake sediment. Potential whiteing event occuring. Microcystin ID: M210111. Probe: 62981. Net: Tow

GPS: 52.54239, -113.99835. Wind: 13 km/h S-SE. Waves: 0.3 m. Whiteing event still occuring, however secchi is slightly deeper than July event. Quite windy at profile, less wind in South side of the lake. Minimal particles observed in the water. Microcystin ID: M210143. Probe: 62981. Net: Tow

GPS: 52.54239, -113.99835. Wind: 9 km/h S-SW. Waves: 0.15 m. Relatively calm day on lake. Whiteing event is starting to subside, secci depth increased from last event in August and the water looks less emerald. Minimal particles noted on surface. Probe might have been off for redox readings, very low compared to other months (using a different probe today). Microcystin ID: M210129. Probe: 47486. Net: Tow

GPS: 52.66798, -111.32806. Wind: 8 km/h N-NW. Waves: 0.02 m. Very quick sampling, even doing three hauls. Look for better bath map back in office. Euthotic depth changed to bottom depth. No other boats on the water today. Volunteer also noted that water levels are eleveated this year and water around his dock was quite clear. 24 ORP at 5 m likely in sediment. Microcystin ID: M210089. Probe: 62981. Net: Tow

GPS: 52.66798, -111.32806. Wind: 24 km/h S. Waves: 0.15 m. Relatively windy but equitment was able to be put in the water column vertically. Athough turbidity was high, no cyanobacteria or algae noted in water to surface. Drifted from the profile location during probe reading (deeper). Went back to location for the rest of the samples. Sediment sample taken from profile. Microcystin ID: M210112. Probe: 62981. Net: Tow

GPS: 52.66798, -111.32806. Wind: 20 km/h NW. Waves: 0.1 m. Calm on the lake. Volunteer reported that cyanobacteria was possibly noticed on the lake a week prior so took 2 grab samples (one on east and west shore at 0.5 m). Potential cyanobacteria particles noted throughout the water, but no high concentration/clumping was noted. Very windy in last 2 days, so may have mixed up the lake. Microcystin ID: M210144. Probe: 62981. Net: Tow

GPS: 52.66798, -111.32806. Wind: 25 km/h NW. Waves: 0.1 m. Although winds were a little high, waves on the lake were minimal and it did not interfere with sampling. Water was quite turbid, some particles noted in the water. Microcystin ID: M210130. Probe: 62981. Net: Tow

GPS: 53.63374. -114.69782. Wind: 17 km/h SE. Waves: 0.05 m. Nice sunny afternoon. Wind was slightly stronger than anticipated (~10 km/h) but did not interfere with sampling. Particles of cyanobacteria (gleotrichia) floating throughout the water column. Microcystin ID: M210092. Probe: 62981. Net: Tow

GPS: 53.63374, -114.69782. Wind: 7 km/h S-SW. Waves: 0.1 m. Grass clippings cyanobacteria (aphanizomenon) floating throughout water to surface. Warm day. Not very busy on the lake. Julian date should have been 193 instead of 199. Sediment sample taken at the profile. Microcystin ID: M210115. Probe: 62981. Net: Tow

GPS: 53.63374, -114.69782. Wind: 15 km/h NW. Waves: 0.05 m. Aphanizomenon particles abundant throughout the lake surface, many have been blown around by the high winds in the last few days. Microcystin ID: M210147. Probe: 62981. Net: Tow

GPS: 53.63374, -114.69782. Wind: 6 km/h N. Wind: 0.1 m. Calm day on lake. Cyanobacteria particles throughout water (aphanizomenon) but volunteer noted they only saw cyanobacteria accumulation along shore about 3 times during the summer. May have started to hit sediment at ~6.0 m, hard bottom at 6.3 m. Sun came out and clouds dissipated around halfway through sampling. Volunteer noted that perhaps in the future we should have more sample points on the West side of the lake. Microcystin ID: M210133. Probe: 62981. Net: Tow

GPS: 53.47932, -114.25501. Wind: 15 km/h NE. Waves: 0.2 m. Noticed clearer water than normal according to the volunteer. New development on the Southeast end of the lake newly approved for development. Windy at some sites but wind died down. Sampling with Keith Tilley. Microcystin ID: M210037. Probe: 49593. Net: Tow

GPS: 53.47932, -114.25501. Wind: 17 km/h NE. Waves: 0.02 m. Calm day on the water. Lots of Loons with chicks. Thick sediment at the bottom. Mussel hauls taken at the profile, in the North basin (North Arm), and at the site closest to the public boat launch. Sampling with Allyson Tilley.

GPS: 53.47932, -114.25501. Wind: 13 km/h NW. Waves: 0.1 m. 3rd sampling event with Keith Tilley and Caleb Sinn. Water at the profile was more green/brown. Water in the North Arm was green. AIS houls taken at the profile, North Arm and boat launch. Not alot of large cyanobacteria in the water. Water has dropped since July sampling but water quality was not diminished significantly. QC of G2 samples taken in triplicate. Microcystin ID: M210038. Probe: 49593. Net: Tow

GPS: 53.47932, -114.25501. Wind: 18 km/h NW. Waves: 0.15 m. 4th sampling trip to Jackfish lake with Allyson. Wind gusts at profile so we used 2 anchors to stabilize boat. Water was moderately turbid with a brown colour. Thunderstorm the night before. Microcystin ID: M210039. Probe: 49593. Net: Tow

GPS: 54.25909, -110.74581. Wind: 13 km/h W. Waves: 0.1 m. First sampling trip with Paul on a canoe. Water had alot of Aphanizomenon. Lots of birds on the lake. There were areas with thick weeds growing. Water level has risen significantly over the past five years. Microcystin ID: M210076. Probe: 49593. Net: Tow

GPS: 54.25909, -110.74581. Wind: 9 km/h NW. Waves: 0.05 m. Lake was lower than last sampling trip and plants at the shoreline were dead. Cyanobacteria throughout with some evidence of decaying surface scum. AIS samples taken at the profile, Northwest end, and near the submerged bridge. Sediment haul taken. Odour present when wind was gusting. Microcystin ID: M210077. Probe: 49593. Net: Tow

GPS: 54.25909, -110.74581. Wind: 17 km/h SW. Waves: 0.15 m. 3rd sampling trip on Jessie Lake with Paul. Cyanobacteria all around the lake planktonically (Aphanizomenon). Highest concentration in the west side. Less floating plants than June and July sampling events. Lots of birds. AIS hauls taken at the profile, the Northeast end, and near the submerged bridge. Metal sample taken at profile at 0.5m (21SWE01277). QC of G2 samples taken in triplicate. Microcystin ID: M210078. Probe: 49593. Net: Tow

GPS: 54.25909. -110.74581. Wind: 20 km/h W. Waves: 0.5 m. 4th sampling trip with Paul. Was windy to start then calmed down. Muskrats near shore. Many coots on the water. Less green than previous months. Microcystin ID: M210079. Probe: 49593. Net: Tow
surface grab - metals

Station: LAC STE. ANNE, EAST SIDE COMPOSITE
SampleComment: GPS: 53.7074822, -114.4029562. Wind: 20 km/h SE. Waves: 0.15 m. Wind speed and direction changing throughout morning. Started from SE and changed to coming from NW by the end of sampling. Wind died down by the time we were returning to dock. Microcystin ID: M210090. Probe: 62981. Net: Tow

Station: LAC STE. ANNE, EAST SIDE COMPOSITE
SampleComment: GPS: 53.71011, -114.39696. Wind: 4 km/h E-SE. Waves: 0.20 m. Cyanobacteria visible (grass clippings) to surface of lake. Sampling event followed week of +30 weather. Water appears to be very well mixed throughout. Saw 6 whitefish dead on the surface of the water. Sediment sample taken at the profile. Microcystin ID: M210113. Probe: 62981. Net: Tow

Station: LAC STE. ANNE, EAST SIDE COMPOSITE
SampleComment: GPS: 53.71011, -114.39696. Wind: 17 km/h N-NW. Waves: 0.3 m. Water has dropped significantly since July sampling (3 ft). Wind gusts made it hard to stay out at profile so we hit bottom at 7.5 m before moving back to the deep spot and finishing the profile readings (redox at 7.5 m and 8.0 m is not accurate). Volunteer mentioned that they had more fish wash up dead at their beach in July (60-100). Cyanobacteria particles throughout water (Aphanozomenon). Microcystin ID: M210145. Probe: 62981. Net: Tow

Station: LAC STE. ANNE, EAST SIDE COMPOSITE
SampleComment: GPS: 53.71011, -114.39696.Wind: 13 km/h W-NW. Waves: 0.2 m. Relatively calm morning. Were able to find a slightly deepter spot at profile. Particles noted in water, no clumping however. Microcystin ID: M210131. Probe: 62981. Net: Tow

SampleComment: GPS: 52.430749, -113.797388. Wind: 25 km/h NW. Waves: 0.15 m. At profile the plant depth = 3.1 m. Lots of plants making composite sampling difficult. Average depth of comp sample = 1 m. Slightly windy for sampling, probe stayed vertical in water column though. Microcystin ID: M210091. Probe: 62981. Net: Tow

GPS: 52.430749, -113.797388. Wind: 17 km/h SE. Waves: 0.05 m. Volunteered noted that water level has dropped ~ 1 ft since June sampling. Plants were closer to the surface and made it difficult to sample. Water was calm. Smoky and rainy day. Sampling event followed a few weeks of + 30 weather. Sediment sample taken at the profile. Microcystin ID: M210114. Probe: 62981. Net: Tow

GPS: 52.430749, -113.797388. Wind: 9 km/h W-NW. Wind: 0.01 m. Light rain while sampling. Too many weeds (Chara) in NW portion of the lake so sampled in the middle. Likely hit the bottom at 3 m in very soft material. Water was quite clear, no particles noted throughout water. Water was a few incles below July sampling event. Microcystin ID: M210146. Probe: 62981. Net: Tow

GPS: 52.430749, -113.797388. Wind: 10 km/h W. Waves: 0.1 m. Started hitting sediment at 2.9 m, hard bottom at 3.2 m. Wind started picking up through morning. 13 km/h by the time we had finished sampling. Microcystin ID: M210132. Probe: 62981. Net: Tow

GPS: 54.430371, -112.755682. Wind: 25 km/h W. Waves: 0.3 m. Rainy day on the water. 1st sampling event with Ron Zurawell. Microcystin ID: M210044. Probe: 49593. Net: Tow

GPS: 54.430371, -112.755682. Wind: 11 km/h W. Waves: 0.01 m. 2nd sampling trip on Long Lake with Ron Zurawell. Dead whitefish at comp site 2. Dead yellow perch near comp site 7. AIS sites at the profile, near day use boat launch, and the North bay. Sediment sample taken at the profile. Microcystin ID: M210045. Probe: 49593. Net: Tow

GPS: 54.430371, -112.755682. Wind: 9 km/h NW. Waves: 0.05 m. 3rd sampling event with Ron Zurawell. Water was very green with streaks in the surface and aphanizomenon. AIS hauls taken at the profile, the day use boat lauch and the North Bay. At the North Bay there were finer particles, harder to condense. QC for G2 were taken in triplicate. Microcystin ID: M210046. Probe: 49593. Net: Tow

GPS: 54.430371, -112.755682. Wind Speed 13 kmh. Wind Direction: W. Waves: 0.10 m. 4th Sampling trip on Long Lake with Ron. Aphanizomenon throughout and amorphous colonies. Tow net. Microcystin ID: M210047

GPS: 54.61028, -110.28426. Wind: 19 km/h E. Waves: 0.5 m. Went with Dean Wood on a pontoon boat. Had to wait for thunderstorm to pass. Very windy at first and second comp site. Dean mentioned water rose in the past two weeks due to rain. Lots of birds on the water. Microcystin ID: M210080. Probe: 49593. Net: Tow

GPS: 54.61028, -110.28426. Wind: 11 km/hr. Waves: 0.5 m. 2nd sampling tip on Marie Lake with Dean. Sampling done after a windy weekend. Clear water with no evidence of cyanobacterial blooms. Obberservations of more leeches this year. AIS mussle hauls taken at the profile, in front of the militart beach and in the south point. Sediment sample taken. Microcystin ID: M210081. Probe: 49593. Net: Tow

GPS: 54.61028, -110.28426. Wind: 7 km/h N. Waves: 0.1 m. 3rd sampling event with Steve, Mark and Tricia. Very Calm morning. AIS hauls taken at the profile, military beach and the South point. Metal sample taken at 9:35 at 0.5 m (21SWE01453). Microcystin ID: M210082. Probe: 49593. Net: Tow

GPS: 54.6103, -110.2843. Wind: 4 km/h S. Waves: 0.2 m. 4th sampling trip with Dean and Pam. Calm water with loons around. Temp was consistent until 20 m. Microcystin ID: M210083. Probe: 49593. Net: Tow
surface grab - metals

GPS: 54.28773, -111.10337. Wind: 15 km/h SW. Waves: 0.05 m. More cattle than in previous years. Concerns about shoreline erosion due to wake boats. Went sampling with Garry Kissel and Caleb Sinn. Some wind but mostly calm conditions. Oxygen presistent deep in the lake. Microcystin ID: M210068. Probe: 49593. Net: Tow

GPS: 54.28773, -111.10337. Wind: 5 km/h NW. Waves: 0.1 m. Surface water was very warm. Lots of dead plants/reedes in surface piles. AIS mussel samples taken at the profile, north site and near the campground. Sediment sample taken at the profile. Microcystin ID: M210069. Probe: 49593. Net: Tow

GPS: 54.28773, -111.10337. Wind: 13 km/h SW. Waves: 0.1 m. 3rd sampling event at Minnie Lake with Garry and Nadeen. Nice morning with wind picking up after the profile site. Water was green but not many cyanobacteria particles in the water. The AIS samples were taked at the profile, North end and campround. Matel sample was taken at the profile at 10:00 (Sample #: 21SWE01287). Microcystin ID: M210070. Probe: 49593. Net: Tow
GPS: 54.28773, -111.10337. Wind: 15 km/h W. Waves: 0.05 m. 4th sampling trip with Garry and Nadeen. Calm morning then gusty. Microcystin ID: M210071. Probe: 49593. Net: Tow
surface grab - metals

GPS: 53.25079, -112.90131. Wind: 9 km/h W. Waves: 0.1 m. Very overcast. In searching for profile location, only found depths of 1.4 m. Conducted composite of surface grab samples to ~0.6 m depth. Microcystin ID: M210093. Probe: 62981. Net: Tow

GPS: 53.25079, -112.90131. Winds: 10 km/h S. Waves: 0.01 m. Calm day. Sampling event followed week of 30+ weather. Very high turbidity. Rocks along shore and in middle of lake were more exposed than trip in June (water level decreased). Microcystin ID: M210106. Probe: 62981. Net: Tow

GPS: 53.25079, -112.90131. Wind: 16 km/h NM. Waves: 0.15 m. Water level ~30 cm lower than July. "Bird Island" has overgrown with plants looks very healthy and pelicans love it. No 1 m check because water level was not high enough. Microcystin ID: M210105. Probe: 62981. Net: Tow

GPS: 53.25079, -112.90131. Wind: 5 km/h S-SW. Waves: 0 m. Tina Mclean assisted with sampling today. Water levels similar as in August. Water green and very turbid. Beautiful full day. Wind picked up towards end of sampling. Birds from the Northern Islands have mainly moved on, but other ducks and migratory birds abundant. Some pelicans. Microcystin ID: M210104. Probe: 62981. Net: Tow

GPS: 53.00766. -114.02466. Winds: 5 km/h S. Waves: 0 m. Lots of midges floating in water. Sampling with Darren, Brittany and Brad. Wind picked up during profile. Thermocline and oxygen spike. 8.0 m bottom grabs for nutrients. 4.5 m phyto grab. Small hole in zoo tow net. Bradley assisted in sampling trip. Microcystin ID: M210094. Probe: 62981. Net: Tow

GPS: 53.00766, -114.02466. Wind: 9 km/h SE. Waves: 0.1 m. Cyanobacteria (gleotrichia)  through water column. Observed whitefish dead on surface (~30 at least). Lake has slight fishy smell. Thin layer of cloud while sampling. PIG194-B 0.1 reading may have been entered to PIG194 file. Took additional sample at 10 m (2 x 250 ml bottles, 1 preserved, 1 not). Sediment sample taken at the profile location.Microcystin ID: M210101. Probe: 62981. Net: Tow. Additional profile taken at buoy 53.019274, -114.020239/

GPS: 5..00766, -114.02466. Wind: 10 km/h W. Waves: 0.05 m. Gleotrichia and aphanizomenon noted in the water column. No dead fish noted on lake, fishy smell almost absent. Cyanobacteria very prominent on surface later in morning (~ 10am) globs and streaks on surface. Mostly around Grandview and provincial park towards the S-SW side of the Lake. Started hitting silty material at about 9.6 m, solid bottom around 10 m. Microcystin ID: M210102. Probe: 62981. Net: Tow. Additional profile recorded at buoy at 53.019274, -114.020239.

GPS: 53.00766. -114.02466. Wind: 13km/h NW. Waves: 0.2 m. Wind increased though sampling, waves quite large. Center site near poplar bay taken slighly closer to Grandview due to waves. Western Grebe spotted in the NW basin. Sampled with Darren. Aphanizomenon moderatly high throughout lake. Clumping most prevalent in NW. Cyanobacteria smell faint, but higher near shorelines. Microcystin ID: M210103. Probe: 62981. Net: Tow. Additional profile taken at buoy at 53.019274, -114.020239.

GPS: 52.07999, -113.43986. Wind: 6 km/h W. Waves: 0.05 m. Beautiful, calm afternoon. Took 2 additional profile samples at AB05CE0890 and AB05CE0960. Microcystin ID: M210095. Probe: 62981. Net: Tow. Profiles also taken this day at other locations: (GPS 52.07047, -113.42204. 21SWE02816.) (GPS: 52.105640, -113.458259. 21SWE02834)

GPS: 52.07880, -113.43822. Wind: 6 km/h S-SE. Waves: 0.01 m. Hot and calm. Lake very busy with wake boats. Lots of phytoplankton, but no visible, distinct colonies. Sampled with Thomas and friend Ryan. AIS at profile, in front of Green Acres, and Leisure campground on North side. eDNA sediment grab at profile. Additional profiles taken at the south and notrh sides. Lots of macrophytes and green algae filaments in water. Microcystin ID: M210109. Probe: 62981. Net: Tow. Profiles also recorded this day at additional locations (GPS: 52.06961, -113.41994. 21SWE03017) (GPS: 52.10542, -113.45869. 21SWE03035)

GPS: 52.07880, -113.43822. Wind: 12 km/hr S-SW. Waves: 0.15 m. Lots of boats on lake, increasing wave height at times, but didn't affect sampling. Cyanobacterial particles noted throughout lake but no accumulation was observed. Hot +30 day. Metal sample taken at profile at 0.5 m. Microcystin ID: M210108. Probe: 62981. Net: Tow. Additional profiles also recorded at: (GPS: 52.07047, -113.42204. 21SWE03376)(GPS: 52.105640, -113.458259. 21SWE03388)

GPS: 52.07880, -113.43822. Wind: 11 km/h SE. Waves: 0.15 m. Rainy morning and gusty but wind was okay at profile, stronger towards North arm of the lake. Started to hit sediment at about 11.4 m and hard bottom at 11.6 m (decided not to get reading at 11.5 m because likely in muck). Took 2 additional profile readings (South and North arms of lake). Volunteer and I decided to go by meters due to cold weather conditions. Particles (likely cyanobacteria) still noted in water. Some cyanobacteria concentrated near docks. Microcystin ID: M210107. Probe: 62981. Net: Tow. (GPS: 52.07047, -113.42204. 21SWE03639) (GPS: 52.105640, -113.458259. 21SWE03648)

GPS: 54.64370, -112.70677. Wind: 11 km/h NW. Waves: 0.1 m. 3rd sampling event with Orest on Skeleton North. Water was very brown with very little cyanobacteria in the water column. AIS samples taken at the profile, west boat launch, and north boat launch. QC samples for G2 taken. Metal sample taken at 0.5 m at 13:45 (sample #: 21SWE01402). Microcystin: M210058. Probe: 49593. Net: Tow

GPS: 54.64370, -112.70677. Wind: 12 km/h W. Waves: 0.05 m. 4th sampling trip with Orest. Quite windy but remained stable because the North is sheltered. Water was quite brown. Microcystin ID: M210057. Probe: 49593. Net: Tow
surface grab - metals
GPS: 54.61106, -112.71704. Wind: 9 km/h SE. Waves: 0.1 m. Went out with Rick. Quiet morning on the water. Water very clear. Microcystin: M210060. Probe: 49593. Net: Tow

GPS: 54.61106, -112.71705. Wind: 5 km/h SE. Waves: 0.1 m. Bloom on the shore (Mewatha beach to the west end). Lots of birds on the water. Bloom moved west while sampling. Smoky out with bright skies. AIS mussel samples taken at the profile, in front of the Bondiss boat launch, and in front of Mewatha boat launch. Sediment sample taken at the profile. Microcystin: M210061. Probe: 49593. Net: Tow

GPS: 54.61106, -112.71704. Wind: 4 km/h SE. Waves: 0.01 m. 3rd sampling event with Rick and his grandson on Skeleton S. Water had many small spherical cyanobacteria around the lake. AIS hauls taken at the profile, at the south east boat launch and Mewatha boat launch. Metal sample was taken at 9:38 at the profile (sample #: 21SWE01226). Microcystin: M210062. Probe: 49593. Net: Tow

GPS: 54.61106, -112.71704. Wind: 9 km/h W. Waves: 0.05 m. 4th sampling event on Skeleton S with Rick. Water had some particles (cyanobacteria colonies) in the water and some blooms near the shore (Mewatha). Microcystin: M210063. Probe: 49593. Net: Tow

GPS: 54.61106, -112.71704. Wind: 12 km/h W. Waves: 0.10 m. 5th sampling trip with Orest. Passed through the narrows to get to the South. Water was mich clearer than before with a brown hue. Wind picked up during the trip so hard to take comp samples in the right spot. Microcystin ID: M210165. Probe: 49593. Net: Tow
surface grab - metals

GPS: 54.65266, -113.77943. Wind: 13 km/h SE. Waves: 0.2 m. Very prevelent algae, worse on the south end. Wind picked up near the end of the sampling trip. Zooplankton net got clogged up so had to tap sides to loosen algae. Microcystin: M210048. Probe: 49593. Net: Tow

GPS: 54.652711, -113.779569. Wind: 13 km/h N. Waves: 0.1 m. 2nd sampling trip with Ron. Water had alot of Aphanizomenon. Cyanobacteria bloom found on north east end of the lake. AIS sampling done at the profile, at the north east bay, and near the outflow (last two were tow hauls). Sediment sample taken at the profile. Microcystin: M210049. Probe: 49593. Net: Tow

GPS: 54.652711, -113.779569. Wind: 10 km/h NW. Waves: 0.5 m. 3rd sampling trip on Steele Lake with Ron. Lake had filamentous cyanobacteria throughout. North-west end had a large surface scum with bright blue colour and a fishy/ ammonia smell. AIS hauls taken at the profile (vertical), the north-east bay (tow) and the outflow (tow). Microcystin: M210050. Probe: 49593. Net: Tow
GPS: 54.652711, -113.779569. Wind: 11 km/h W. Waves: 0.3 m. 4th sampling trip on Steel Lake with Ron. Water had aphanizomenon and amourphous colonies. Microcystin: M210051. Probe: 49593. Net: Tow

SampleComment: GPS: 54.14438, -111.50222. Wind: 7 km/h NW. Waves: 0.2 m Lots of birds on the water. Lots of beaver dams. Signs of Aphanizomenon in the wate rat the profile and south side. Alot of leeches in the water. Microcystin: M210064. Probe: 49593. Net: Tow

GPS: 54.14438, -111.50222. Wind: 7 km/h W. Waves: 0.1 m. 2nd sampling trip with Charity. Aphanizomenon around the lake mostly concentrated on the east side. Dead leeches on the shore. Lots of red zooplankton. All sites were more shallow or less than 1 meter than the euphotic depth. AIS hauls at the profile, near the castle and near the boat launch. Sediment sample taken at the profile. Microcystin: M210065. Probe: 49593. Net: Tow

GPS: 54.14438, -111.50222. Wind: 8 km/h SW. Waves: 0.01 m. 3rd sampling event with Charity. Water had surface scums in the center near the profile and at the water's edge. Particulate aphanizomenon throughout. AIS hauls taked at the profile, near the castle and near the boat launch. Metal sample taken at 6:55 at 0.5 m (sample #: 21SWE01349). Microcystin: M210066. Probe: 49593. Net: Tow

GPS: 54.14438, -111.50222. Wind: 6 km/h SE. Waves: 0.1 m. 4th sampling trip with Charity. Lake had aphanizomenon throughout and gleotrichia around the profile. Microcystin: M210067. Probe: 49593. Net: Tow
surface grab - metals

GPS: 53.5263051, -114.5506487. Wind: 13 km/h E. Waves: 0.1 m. Overcast day, no sun during sampling event. Relatively calm morning, with wind picking up later in morning. Light rain while sampling (but not raining at profile). Microcystin ID: M210096. Probe: 62981. Net: Tow

GPS: 53.53191, -114.56600. Wind: 8 km/h SW. Waves: 0.05 m. Secchi disk broke off in lake. Measured secchi with kemmerer. Noticed multiple whitefish dead on water surface (10-20). Balls of cyanobacteria throughout water column (looks similar to pollen). Noticed very clear streaking on surface in areas. Sampling event followed a week of +30 weather. Microcystin surface grab taken from Sunshine Bay Boat Club (accumulation of cyanobacteria on the surface) with ID: M210154. Sediment sample taken at the profile. Microcystin ID: M210116. Probe: 62981. Net: Tow

GPS: 53.53191, -114.56600. Wind: 13 km/h W-NW. Waves: 0.2 m. Gusty wind at profile (19 km/h gusts) some waves were 0.4-0.5 m. Tried to get readings with probe as vertical as possible. Less windy in NW of lake (Seba Beach). Gleotrichia (likely) noted throughout water but was likely stirred up by the wind. Microcystin ID: M210148. Probe: 62981. Net: Tow

GPS: 53.53191, -114.56600. Wind: 11 km/hr SW. Waves: 0.3 m. Sampling started off calm, only ~0.1 m waves at profile when we started. Waves increased to 0.3 m within minutes as a system started moving in. Wind shifted position at profile and waves made it difficult for depth finder to be accurate. Winds increased to 22 km/h during sampling. Minimal particles noted in water. Microcystin ID: M210134. Probe: 62981. Net: Tow
